The Land Rhineland-Palatinate Bank was instead linked to the Land Bank of Baden-Württemberg in Stuttgart.
But there were always new negotiations on the merger of Deka-Bank with banks in the Länder.
Finally, however, Günther Merl, chairman of the Hellaba Management Committee, was against any business strategy of merging with his bank.
