The Hesse-Thuringia group of savings and credit institutions, which owns 85% of Helaba's capital, however, closed all mergers with WestLB at the beginning of the year.
NordLB would remain in the strictest sense.
Such geostrategic considerations, however, reflect only one facet.
Another aspect is how the different business models of each of these banks can be matched.
