Miss Boyd summed it up by saying that "Zora saved Eatonville".
The victory against the highway project allowed him to change his own image.
Nonresidents, like Rachelle Munson, a lawyer who has been a member of our church since 1993, began to come in large numbers, and residents began to reconsider the past.
Eatonville has been a historic town since 1998.
