In return for his help, Washington will get shares in the rescued companies that will pay dividends if they make a profit and which it can sell when the storm passes.
The Federal Government will be able to delay foreclosure proceedings on housing linked to the mortgage loans covered by this plan and to set limits on the remuneration and severance payments paid to the managers of the companies affected.
